This has been a freakin' long day, yo. Jim has his tonsilectomy today, so he was all fuckin' out of it, and I was a nervous wreck the whole time he was in surgery-so was his dad, though :) But he's all good, he's just gotta stay overnight at the hospital in Hiawatha 'cause he's of adult age and the blood vessels in his throat are bigger. When the doctor was tellin' us what his tonsils were like (full of pus), I was like "Dude, no more." It was sick, and he was about to get sick again, so it's a good thing Dr. Sinning did this though. Jim will be so much healthier for it.

Actually, to tell the truth, this whole freakin' week has been long. I've been lookin' for a job, tryin' to get my car into the place where it's gonna get the new transmission put in, and just tryin' to keep myself busy-which ain't been that hard, 'cause I've been doin' so much stuff. I need to call my mom though, I haven't talked to her since last Sunday..I went to visit her and things just went terrible. I was in tears all the way back home; I just couldn't believe how my mom was actin'. But what can I do but prove to her that this was the right thing for me, since she thinks I made a big mistake. Well, back to the hospital I go :)

You know how Jim and I were livin' at my house? Well you'll never guess where we are now. Just take a guess...If you guessed his house, you are absolutely 100% correct. Yes sirree, we're at his parents' house now. Shit hit the fan with me and my mom, our livin' situation was a lil iffy, and here I am. Sittin' at the family computer, thinkin' about the last week and how my mom and I really haven't spoken. I went to see her Sunday, and it didn't go well. I wish now I hadn't gone all that way to see her, since all she did was make me feel like shit. I should be used to that by now, but I'm not. She's my mom, and if it weren't for her, I wouldn't be typin' this journal entry right now; I'd be in a gutter somewhere waitin' to die. Now I wish I could take back all the horrible, terrible, etc things I said to her, because I never meant them. I love my mother more than words could ever say, but I think I've fucked up royally this time. There's no going back and changing the past; all I can hope for is a good life for everyone that knows me, especially my mom. I never wanted things to be like this; I need my mom like I need air. Without her, I don't know how I'll go on. It's sad, me talkin' like this-like my mom's dead, but it's true--our relationship is shattered to such an extent that I don't know if it's repairable. I can't count how many times I wish I had taken all of my mom's prescription pills three or four years ago on the anniversary of my grandma's death; I had them in my hand, I was ready to just swallow those capsules and wait for Death himself to come for me, but I didn't do a thing. I called a friend and here I am right now, telling you about it all. If I wasn't here, I wouldn't be putting anyone through any kind of stress or heartbreak. But all I can do now is pick up the pieces and move on...

Well, guess what..Me and Jim are livin' together. Ain't it cool? Well, I mean, he moved into my mom's house with us, 'cause his parents are all fucked up in the head, not like schizo bad, just they-don't-feel-like-bein'-parents. **Haha, I had y'all thinkin' we'd shacked up together and gotten married. Nah, that comes later LOL!!! Haha, fooled ya again. Me, married-HELL NAH, FOO!!!** They kicked him out last night and he ended up at my house around 3:30. It's crazy shit, but it's all good. It'll be fun havin' him with me all the time, since we never get to see each other. Now we'll prally get tired of each other and start bitchin' like an old married couple. I just can't get over the fact that my mom's even lettin' him stay with us-not cause she's a bad person, just the fact that it's my boyfriend and she knows we hop on the good foot and do the bad thing every so often heeheehee **devil horns**. Oh well, we're legal, and it's good exercise and it's free, so we don't have to spend any money, except for when we go on a condom run. Hey, at least we're protected, right? :)

Anyways, I'm kinda tired and I don't feel like writin' as much as I usually, so..umm..yeah..

I hate liars. I hate thiefs. I hate cheaters...and I know somebody that does all three things. Terrible, ain't it? This particular person will never be named, because I label them as an "Unmentionable"-the type of person whose name should never be said and whose face should never be seen; there's quite a few people on that list of mine :). I can't believe that one person could ever make me feel like I could just scream and cry and go completely fuckin' bonkers, to put it bluntly. Obviously I care(d) about this person, but all that's straight out the window. Maybe the care will grow a pair of wings and fly to someone that really deserves it..the Unmentionable that I'm talkin' about sure isn't gettin' it back, no matter what happens...

Don't worry, I'm sure it's nobody that's readin' this..I highly doubt the Unmentionable even noticed that this exists, since this person doesn't even realize that I exist most of the time. It's definitely not Jim or any of my close friends *like Nortney, Loreal, Tuna, or Ashler*, and it's not really family, although there's a couple people in the family who are listed as Unmentionables, and they know who they are, I'm sure.

**Sarcasm alert**>>Well last night was entirely too much fun **sarcasm alert over**...cruisin' on "The Strip", yellin' at stupid people like Stephany to move her ass 'cause she drives slower than shit and she likes to talk so much shit, but not back it up. But the only thing wrong with the whole night was the fact that Jim promised me he was comin' down here, but of course, like most guys, he broke that promise. Not a biggie or anything, it just really pissed me off. So maybe it was a blessin' in disguise that Stephany aka I'm-Always-Pregnant-And-I-Don't-Know-Who-The-Baby's-Daddy-Is-So-Basically-That-Makes-Me-A-Whore didn't say anything other than the stuff she was talkin', otherwise I think the combination of me bein' hella mad at Jim and bein' pissed off at my mom prally woulda been quite explosive heeheehee. I'm still tryin' to figure out what to do for Thanksgiving..so many options..haha, yeah right, that's a laugh. But all in all, it's good times and I ain't really worryin' about anything, because if I do that, then that'll just upset everyone, and that's the last thing I wanna do.

I'm not mad at Jim anymore, which is a good thing..he came over to my house and apologized to me and gave me some flowers-my favorites, yellow roses, no less :D I was like, what in the world did I ever do to deserve this. You know what he said..he said that just bein' me and lovin' him and acceptin' him for who he is was the reason he did that. I about started cryin', but then I didn't want my mama pickin' on me for bein' a silly girl :-p I'm just the luckiest girl in the world to have him, and I love him a lot..not more than my mommy, even though she's the biggest bitch on the planet most of the time, or Jesus, but he's right up there for sure :)

Man, I don't even have a clue as to what to put in here..I guess I'll just start with my life as of right now..Well, Jim *the bestest boyfriend in the whole entire universe* and I were out and about, and we ran into Lori and Tara *two of my best friends*..We hung out some, and then they met up with some guy friends of Heather and Scott *two of my friends..I guess, even though they're so into each other that they're not really aware that friends even exist anymore..It's all about them..*. We told them to meet us at Stage's parkin' lot at 10:00..right?? WRONG apparently, 'cause they didn't even show up, and we waited 15(!!) extra minutes. I was like, that's fucked up, but I didn't really think about it, 'cause then I went and got me some, ya know what I'm sayin' ;)...Yesterday I talked to my friend Jimmy. Hadn't talked to him in about forever and a day. He's an aspirin' filmmaker and musician, so that's what he SAYS he's been doin'..I say he's been doin' Rachel, his ex-girlfriend. But he swears up and down and around and around that he's STILL a virgin..at 20 years old. Which, if it were actually true, would be really respectable in my humble and biased opinion, but I think he's lyin' to me..I don't know though. Maybe I still have feelings for him, maybe I don't..I love Jim way too much to fuck it up with Jimmy, but eventually I'm gonna have to sort all of it out, and that's gonna hurt worse than any physical pain I could possibly imagine. When feelings get thrown into the midst of a situation, all you can do is go with what your heart tells you..and my heart is kind of goin'every which way and then some-on every single problem in my life. It'll all get sorted out in the end, but it's gonna hurt me more than I could possibly imagine, i'm sure...

My mom and I have been fightin' a lot lately..we've never really been close, although she's been my only parent and I'm the only child. I don't know what it is..I think it's the fact that I'm now 18 and I'm free to do as I please-I'm an independent woman, and I think that scares her. Of course her extreme depression and lack of work wouldn't play into it at all, would it? But who knows? The only person I can think of that knows all about everything in my life and why it is the way it is would be Jesus, and if that's the case, he needs to help me out some more dammit LOL :-p.
